Popular Nigerian pop star, David Adeleke, also known as Davido, has given due credit to his fellow singer, Augustine Miles Kelechi, popularly known as Tekno for reviving his career at the moment he needed it most. Davido said he didn’t have any hit songs for almost a year until Tekno came and brought him back to the spotlight. The 29-year-old revealed that his hit song, ‘IF’ was written by Tekno. Davido disclosed this to Ebuka Obi-Uchendu on the Bounce Radio program. He said: “Till date, I am still grateful to Tekno. Tekno brought me back, I didn’t have a hit for almost a year. “Tekno wrote the song “IF” and he wanted me to record the song. He wanted me to do it because I am a good guy.” Video:   A post shared by Our Talk Room (@ourtalkroom) 